Notes: The 'row_id' uniquely identifies each measurement, making 'hasIdentifier' the most appropriate property to map this column.
Patient ID directly relates to the patient associated with the measurement, making this path semantically suitable.
Measurement code represents a coded value, mapping to the 'Code' class, is semantically appropriate.
Measurement value is a quantitative result, best mapped to 'Quantity' to capture numeric data with units.
Units specify the measurement scale, making 'hasUnit' the most semantically accurate property.
Measurement date is a dateTime value, directly mapped to the XML Schema dateTime datatype.
